...Slowly, over more than 15 years, the profile of seaweed farmers in Zanzibar is changing from just being predominantly female. Men are progressively joining the fray and in some places,  villages as a whole participate in the mariculture of seaweed that are sold dry to exporters to carrageenan manufacturers in the US, Denmark, France and on a smaller scale to Spain, China and Vietnam.

